<p>[3]Koepsell TD, Wolf ME, Buchner DM, Kukull WA, LaCroix AZ, Tencer AF, Frankenfeld CL, Tautvydas M, Larson EB. Footwear style and risk of falls in older adults. J Am Geriatr Soc. 2004 Sep;52(9):1495-501. doi: 10.1111/j.1532-5415.2004.52412.x. PMID: 15341551. </p>
<p>[4]Harvard Health. 10 tips for finding the right shoes </p>
<p>https://www.health.harvard.edu/staying-healthy/10-tips-for-finding-the-right-shoes#:~:text=If%20one%20foot%20is%20larger,press%20forward%20as%20you%20w </p>
<p>[5]Kim, N., Do, W. Developing elderly men’s footwear sizing system based on their foot shapes. Fash Text 6, 28 (2019). https://doi.org/10.1186/s40691-019-0184-2 </p>
